Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.46,0:14:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们焦虑的时候,我们的大脑并不会理智的思考,\N即使我们面前只是好喝啤酒,\N 它也只想让我赶紧离开让它不安的地方.是的,这是另外的问题了\Nwe're when we're anxious our brains shut off rational thinking right it doesn't want us wondering is that a nice bear just wants us getting out of there well that's that's and that's an additional problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.50,0:14:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道真诚在沟通中的重要性就是因为真诚和沟通以及思考并没有什么区别\N 所以你问人们是否能独自进行,常规的答案就是不行\N.yo u know part of the reason that Honesty in speech is so important is that there isn't any difference between honesty and speech and thinking so you said can people do this alone and the answer to that generally is no .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.53,0:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,因为思绪本身就是一个对话的过程.我们之间现在进行就是思考,我们与观众一起思考,我们为观众一起思考.because thought itself is generally a dialogical process so what you and I are doing right now is thinking things through now we're doing that with an audience and for an audience
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.48,0:15:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,讨论的之前我们都有自己的想法.\N讨论的时候,我们在相互争论也在配合,我们允许讨论改变我们的想法.所以我们允许讨论改变我们的经历.\Nbut you have some propositions and I have some propositions and we're we're pitting them against each other and cooperating at the same time and we're allowing the discourse to modify  our implicit presuppositions so we're allowing the discourse to modify our stories
